         <abstract>
            <p>A simple computational procedure is developed for accurately summing series of the form Σ&lt;sup&gt;∞&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;k = 0&lt;/sub&gt;(2k + 1)&lt;sup&gt;-p&lt;/sup&gt;z&lt;sup&gt;2k + 1&lt;/sup&gt;, where z is complex with |z| ≤ 1 and p = 2 or 3, as well as series of the type &lt;tex-math&gt;$\sum^\infty_{k = 0} (2k + 1)^{-p} \cosh(2k + 1)x/\cosh(2k + 1)b$&lt;/tex-math&gt; and &lt;tex-math&gt;$\sum^\infty_{k = 0} (2k + 1)^{-p} \sinh(2k + 1)x/\cosh(2k + 1)b$&lt;/tex-math&gt;, where 0 ≤ x ≤ b, p = 2 or 3. The procedures are particularly useful in cases where the series converge slowly. Numerical experiments illustrate the effectiveness of the procedures.</p>
          </abstract>
